  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Blitz the tomatoes smooth with a stick blender. Pour into a sauce pan and bring to boil, turn down heat and simmer for 5-6 mins, season with salt."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Mix water and flour in a bowl, combine till shaggy, leave for 30 mins (this is the autolyse) makes it easier to knead and gives the dough strength."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Crumble in yeast and turn out onto a cold surface. Knead to combine yeast. Then add salt and knead to combine until the dough is smooth and elastic."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "At this point I would leave the dough for anywhere between 24 and 72 hours in the fridge."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "On the day you using it divide into 8 equal amounts (115g each) and roll into tight balls. Leave to prove again at room temp for 4-6 hours."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour 1L veg oil into large deep metal pot, heat to 200°C."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Stretch out the dough balls into pizza shapes (as round as possible) and the correct size for your pan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "With two hands gently drop the stretched dough into the oil (drop away from your to avoid getting flicked with hot oil)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Use a metal spoon to adjust the dough if it has folded on top of itself."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Fry until golden occasionally turning the dough over so both sides are evenly cooked."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drain on a bit of kitchen roll/blue roll."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Top with the tomato sauce, then ⅓ buratta each, then a few pieces of artichoke and some Calabrian chili with its oil, tear up a few basil leaves then a sprinkle of flaky salt and you’re done!"
    }
  ],
